own urine, or red or black stools.', 'Distribution', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/122355/', '[1] Udall JA "Warfarin-chloral hydrate interaction." Ann Intern Med 81 (1974): 341-4[2] Orme M, Breckenridge A, Brooks RV "Interactions of benzodiazepines with warfarin." Br Med J 3 (1972): 611-4[3] Cucinell SA, Odessky L, Weiss M, Dayton PG "The effect of chloral hydrate on bishydroxycoumarin metabolism." JAMA 197 (1966): 144-6[4] Udall JA "Warfarin interactions with chloral hydrate and glutethimide." Curr Ther Res Clin Exp 17 (1975): 67-74[5] Wells PS, Holbrook AM, Crowther NR, Hirsh J "Interactions of warfarin with drugs and food." Ann Intern Med 121 (1994): 676-83[6] Boston Coll Drug Surv Prog "Interaction between chloral hydrate and warfarin." N Engl J Med 286 (1972): 53-6[7] Sellers EM, Koch-Weser J "Potentiation of warfarin-induced hypoprothrombinemia by chloral hydrate." N Engl J Med 283 (1970): 827-31[8] Udall JA "Clinical implications of warfarin interactions with five sedatives." Am J Cardiol 35 (1975): 67-71[9] Robinson DS, Sylwester D "Interaction of commonly prescribed drugs and warfarin." Ann Intern Med 72 (1970): 853-6[10] "Product Information. Fycompa (perampanel)." Eisai Inc, Teaneck, NJ.[11] Gilman AG, Rall TW, Nies AS, Taylor P, eds. "Goodman and Gilman''s the Pharmacological Basis of Therapeutics. 8th ed." New York, NY: Pergamon Press Inc. (1990):[12] Warrington SJ, Ankier SI, Turner P "Evaluation of possible interactions between ethanol and trazodone or amitriptyline." Neuropsychobiology 15 (1986): 31-7[13] "Product Information. Rexulti (brexpiprazole)." Otsuka American Pharmaceuticals Inc, Rockville, MD.[14] Bodiford AB, Kessler FO, Fermo JD, Ragucci KR "Elevated international normalized ratio with the consumption of grapefruit and use of warfarin." SAGE Open Med Case Rep 0 (2013): 1-3[15] Guo LQ, Yamazoe Y "Inhibition of cytochrome P450 by furanocoumarins in grapefruit ju